Aims & Questions BAckground
design
meAsures
Show how university support for short-term placements
can promote positive learning processes in relation to
reection skills of student teachers.
(1) Evaluating a seminar designed to foster student
teachers reection competences
(2) Assessing student teachers reection com-
petence by using reection reports during their
practical assignment
(3) Exploring correlations between reection com-
petence and pedagogical beliefs
Quasi-experimental study in a one-group pre-test-post-
test design
Experimental group of student teachers (n=30)
Control group of student teachers (n=30)
(a) pedagogical-psychological knowledge (BilWiss 2.0)
(b) Transmissive and constructivist beliefs (BilWiss 2.0
(c) Theory-based reection reports (EDAMA)
(d) Pupils feedback (Bodensohn et al., 2008 + Helmke et
al., 2017)
